  "text": "Using a WAGO PLC with two 750-502 digital dual output modules [CITATION_1] , simple Pulse Width Modulation (PWM) control can be exercised. When the duct is to be used as a pump, class D modulation allows control of both duty cycle and frequency. These parameters can be used to determine the flow rate and flow direction as shown in Table 2 . Exact pulse parameters are however subject to tube dimensions and carbonyl iron content of the MAP. At 4 Hz and above, pump motion ceases regardless of the pulse width.",
